@next p4ng/pattern-priming

! instantiated-by: Borrow the Situation
  + context: You are using prompts to guide group inquiry.
    + if: The provided situation feels flat or generic.
    + but: Participants want meaningful relevance.
    + then: Invite participants to select, remix, or define their own prompts.
    + because: Co-defined challenges increase contextual fit and engagement.
  + evidence-base:
      - User-centered design stresses co‐defining the design challenge.
      - Participatory futures methods encourage situational remixing to deepen ownership.


