! instantiated-by: Pattern Priming
  + context: Participants may be new to design patterns.
    + if: You want them to identify and name patterns in real time.
    + but: The concept of a “pattern” feels abstract.
    + then: Seed early, light-touch examples (“What did you just do that worked?”) to build intuitive fluency.
    + because: Surfacing tacit knowledge enables double-loop learning.
  + evidence-base:
      - Cognitive apprenticeship models show the value of modelling strategy before expecting application.
      - Argyris & Schön emphasize reflection on action as enabling pattern recognition.


