@next p4ng/role-reveal

! instantiated-by: Timebox the Core
  + context: You have limited workshop time (60–120 minutes).
    + if: You want to complete a full PLACARD loop.
    + but: Time or cognitive load may cause overload.
    + then: Identify a minimal viable loop and simplify peripheral steps.
    + because: Time constraints sharpen focus and support iterative learning.
  + evidence-base:
      - Agile retrospectives and sprint practices use timeboxing to enhance focus.
      - Facilitation research highlights that scoped cycles improve group clarity.


